{"content":"<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">Celebrating their 30th anniversary, Frostmoon Eclipse breathes new life into their seminal album “Gathering the Dark” with a remaster and fresh artwork. Originally recorded in 2001, this album captures the raw essence of mid-90s black metal while incorporating unique acoustic elements and diverse melodic passages. The release marks a significant milestone in the Italian black metal scene, available for the first time on vinyl and as part of an exclusive 4-disc CD boxset.</p><p class='lead'><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>A Dark and Ethereal Journey</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">Embarking on “Gathering the Dark (Alternate Version)” by Frostmoon Eclipse feels like stepping into a shadowy, uncharted realm. The opener, “Where No Light Burns”, immediately grips you with its intense riffs, a stark reminder of heavy metal’s core. The ambient break at 3:59 is a breathtaking shift, blending haunting beauty with raw power before diving back into the brutal onslaught of pounding drums and visceral screams. The album continues to impress with “Worms on Mankind”, which kicks off with a thrash-inspired riff that nods to metal’s roots while staying refreshingly current. This fusion of old-school thrash and Frostmoon Eclipse’s distinctive black metal style creates a dynamic and exhilarating experience. Tracks like “Ashes” and “Ruins” add a medieval ambiance, crafting vivid soundscapes that transport listeners to ancient, battle-scarred lands. The seamless integration of acoustic elements enhances the album’s atmosphere without compromising its ferocity.</p><p class='lead'><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>30 Years of Black Metal Excellence</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">In celebration of their 30th anniversary in 2024, Frostmoon Eclipse delves into their roots with the remastered gem “Gathering the Dark”. First unveiled in 2001, this album showcases their significant influence on the black metal genre. Featuring talents from renowned bands such as Darvaza and Deathrow, it combines melodic passages, acoustic guitars, and intense blast beats with harsh, demonic vocals. Remastered by Davide Gorrini and adorned with new artwork, this release stands as a testament to Frostmoon Eclipse’s enduring legacy and is a must-have for any black metal enthusiast.</p>","title":"ALBUM REVIEW: \"Gathering the Dark (Alternate Version)\" by Frostmoon Eclipse — An Old-School Black Metal Gem Reborn","details":"Where no Light Burns [05:28]; Worms on Mankind [06:04]; Dragon Millennium [05:07]; Ashes [01:13]; I am My Worst Enemy [05:59]; Let the World Burn [04:48]; Dusk to Exalt My Triumph [05:35]; Ruins [01:58].","Socials":"\n<p class='lead'>\n  <a href='123'><i class='bi bi-facebook'></i></a>\n  \n  \n  \n</p>","img01":"https://pulse-of-the-underground.com/assets/a1615728745_10.jpg","sub":"gbK4OvgKbyYDfYCfIjboOqjA9Yv1","date":"17/06/2024","lang":"en","translations":{"en":"ALBUM-REVIEW:-Gathering-the-Dark-(Alternate-Version)-by-Frostmoon-Eclipse--An-Old-School-Black-Metal-Gem-Reborn.json"},"category":"Latest Reviews(ENG)","isReady":true,"written_date":"17/06/2024"}